Run the complete ADE SDLC cycle for: $ARGUMENTS

Follow the 10-phase ADE workflow:

## Phase 0 — INTENT
Extract structured requirements: type (feature/bugfix/refactor), goal, acceptance criteria, affected areas, estimated scope (S/M/L).
Save to `.ade/tasks/<task-id>/intent.md`.

## Phase 1 — RESEARCH
Launch up to 3 Explore agents in parallel to investigate:
1. Existing implementation — files, functions, execution paths
2. Related patterns — how similar features work elsewhere
3. Reusable utilities — shared helpers, hooks, components

## ◆ USER GATE
STOP. Present research findings and proposed approach.
Get explicit approval before proceeding.

## Phase 2 — PLAN
Write implementation plan to `.ade/tasks/<task-id>/plan.md` with:
1. Context — why this change is being made
2. Ordered task list — dependency-aware
3. Files to create/modify — table with paths and descriptions
4. Dependencies — new packages, env vars
5. Test strategy
6. Risk areas

## ◆ PLAN GATE
Verify plan is complete. Do NOT proceed if incomplete.

## Phase 3 — DESIGN CHECK
Dispatch a Sonnet subagent in a worktree to create file stubs:
`Agent(model="sonnet", isolation="worktree", prompt="Create stubs based on plan...")`
Review stubs for plan alignment.

## Phase 4 — IMPLEMENT
Dispatch 1-3 Sonnet subagents in the worktree. Each agent owns specific files — no overlap.
Enforce build order: shared types → backend → frontend.

## Phase 5 — QUALITY GATE
Dispatch a Haiku subagent to run build + tests.
If failures, dispatch a Sonnet fixer subagent (max 3 attempts).

## Phase 6 — REVIEW
Launch 3 parallel Sonnet review subagents:
1. Logic: errors, edge cases, null handling, race conditions
2. Conventions: project patterns, naming, structure (from CLAUDE.md)
3. Security: OWASP top 10, injection, auth bypass, secrets

Classify findings: HIGH (blocking) / MEDIUM (fix before merge) / LOW (advisory).
Fix all HIGH and MEDIUM before proceeding.

## Phase 7 — VERIFY
Run the full test suite. For UI changes, capture screenshots.
Verify each acceptance criterion from Phase 0.

## Phase 8 — DOCUMENTATION
Update affected docs: product capabilities, architecture, API docs.

## Phase 9 — COMMIT & PR
Stage files, commit with conventional message, push, open PR.

## ◆ MERGE GATE
Present PR to user for review and merge decision.

## Phase 10 — RETROSPECTIVE
Record: cycle time per phase, iteration counts, what worked, what didn't.
Save to `.ade/tasks/<task-id>/retro.json`.
Clean up worktree after merge.

## Circuit Breakers
- Design check: max 2 iterations
- Code→review loop: max 3 cycles
- QA fix: max 3 iterations
- Verify→review: max 2 cycles
After any limit, escalate to user. Do NOT retry silently.

## Orchestrator Rules
- The orchestrator NEVER writes application code — only dispatches subagents
- All code changes flow through subagents
- Verify subagent output independently — don't trust self-reports
- Update `.ade/tasks/<task-id>/status.md` at each phase transition
